rComments: Jeff is a great professor and very nice person. Very accessible and helpful in office hours and does not shame for asking questions. He doesn't like when people skip tutorials and/or class, but if you go to class, tutorials, and genuinely put in the effort, you should be fine.
Jeff is a great professor. While he has high expectations, hes always willing to try his best to help. Be sure to study outside hard of class and get ready to put in effort.
His lectures are not the best but he's a good person and willing to help in office hours.

Jeff is a great prof once you get to know him. Yeah he's not perfect, but you could tell he tries his best. He takes into effect any advice you give and always welcomes feedback. And from experience, he almost always incorporates the feedback. If you don't understand a topic, he'll try his best to help you even if that means staying late.

A funny and smart guy, but the lack of teaching experience really showed. The lectures felt disorganized and a little rushed. His writing is pretty small. If you've never done linear algebra before, the lectures can be hard to follow. He usually doesn't show his work because he assumes you've learned a handful of the material from high school.

He is an awful prof. He is so dull and boring you will fall asleep in class. He expects you to know stuff in math that you are actually supposed to be learning from him. His writing is chicken scratch, and overall just a terrible prof. They post online lectures so if you are stuck with him just watch those.
